Title: Data Analyst
Description:
About The Opportunity

A remote-first technology company operating in the SaaS analytics and data intelligence sector, building data products and dashboards that drive product, growth, and revenue decisions. We convert raw data into trusted insights by designing scalable ETL pipelines, dashboards, and KPI reporting used by cross-functional teams.

Primary Title: Data Analyst | Location: Remote — Canada | Company: Fireno

Role & Responsibilities


Design, develop, and maintain ETL pipelines and data transformations to ensure timely, clean, and reliable datasets for analytics and reporting.
Write optimized SQL queries and Python scripts to extract, analyze, and validate large datasets from relational and cloud-native data stores.
Create interactive dashboards and visualizations (Tableau/Power BI) that surface KPIs, trends, and actionable insights for product, sales, and executive stakeholders.
Collaborate with product managers and engineers to define measurement frameworks, design A/B test analyses, and translate business questions into analytical approaches.
Perform ad-hoc and recurring analyses—cohort, funnel, retention, and revenue analyses—to inform strategic decisions and roadmap prioritization.
Document data definitions, maintain data quality checks, and implement monitoring to ensure consistency and trust in reporting outputs.


Skills & Qualifications

Must-Have


SQL
Python
Excel
Tableau
Power BI
ETL
Data Modeling
Statistical Analysis


Preferred


Google BigQuery
Snowflake
Looker


Benefits & Culture Highlights


Fully remote, Canada-based role with flexible hours and asynchronous collaboration.
Opportunity to own end-to-end analytics projects that directly impact product and growth strategy.
Collaborative, data-driven culture with mentorship and clear career progression for analysts.


This role is ideal for a detail-oriented analyst who enjoys transforming complex data into clear, high-impact insights. To apply, include examples of dashboards or analyses (screenshots or links) and a brief note on tools used and impact delivered.

Skills: sql,statistical analysis,data modeling,excel,python,tableau,power bi,etl

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Requisition ID: 238906

Join a purpose driven winning team, committed to results, in an inclusive and high-performing culture.

High quality data is critical to the success of Scotia Global Asset Management (SGAM). There is a strategic vision across SGAM to transform the way in which data is managed through the creation of centralized data hubs. This has several benefits, including the ability for enhanced analytics to support decision making, improved operational efficiency, risk reduction, decreased vendor costs, and building the foundation for the future.

In this role, you will be responsible for the implementation of our SGAM Data Hub. This will focus on centralizing and creating a single source of truth for asset management back-office and operational data, including but not limited to custodian, fund accounting, fund profile, and Morningstar data. You will also be working with business and technology partners across SGAM on new data and reporting initiatives and delivery of data quality enhancements.

Is this role right for you? In this role you will:


Design, build, and maintain the SGAM Data Hub as it supports Business and Operations needs.
Gather, process, and analyze complex raw data at scale.
Collaborate with integration teams to design and implement system integration solutions, addressing data-related challenges.
Develop test strategies to ensure the reliability and performance of developed solutions.
Interact with Business Analysts and Product Owners for requirement gathering, analysis, and user story grooming.
Prepare comprehensive documentation, including test strategy documents, test case documents, and user story creation.
Work in close collaboration with the entire Project and BAU Support teams to ensure on-time deliverables and project milestones.
Identify and implement internal process improvements to enhance efficiency and reduce time expenses.
Participate in engagement with key partners and stakeholders to understand investment data and reporting requirements and participate in design, planning, testing, and solutions delivery


Do you have the skills that will enable you to succeed in this role? We’d love to work with you if you have.


Bachelor’s degree, with a technology, computer science, or business focus, or equivalent education and experience.
High level of proficiency with enterprise data management platforms. 5+ years of experience is preferred.
High level of proficiency with SQL server, .Net framework, Informatica, Data Stage, Talend, and MSBI, is an asset.
Experience in Agile and DevOps software development methodologies.
Previous experience with core asset management data domains (eg. positions, security reference, pricing, benchmarks, fund data, accounting data, etc.).
Ability to develop positive and collaborative relationships with business partners and effectively communicate with both business and technology data stakeholders.
Excellent organizational skills and a keen attention to detail.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.


What's in it for you?


Diversity, Equity, Inclusion & Allyship - We strive to create an inclusive culture where every employee is empowered to reach their fullest potential, respected for who they are, and are embraced through bias-free practices and inclusive values across Scotiabank. We embrace diversity and provide opportunities for all employee to learn, grow & participate through our various Employee Resource Groups (ERGs) that span across diverse gender identities, ethnicity, race, age, ability & veterans.
Accessibility and Workplace Accommodations - We value the unique skills and experiences each individual brings to the Bank, and are committed to creating and maintaining an inclusive and accessible environment for everyone. Scotiabank continues to locate, remove and prevent barriers so that we can build a diverse and inclusive environment while meeting accessibility requirements.
Upskilling through online courses, cross-functional development opportunities, and tuition assistance.
Competitive Rewards program including bonus, flexible vacation, personal, sick days and benefits will start on day one.
Dynamic Ecosystem - Free tea & coffee, universal washrooms, and lots of space for team collaboration.
Community Engagement - We offer opportunities for community engagement & belonging with our various programs such as hackathons.


Location(s): Canada : Ontario : Toronto

Scotiabank is a leading bank in the Americas. Guided by our purpose: "for every future", we help our customers, their families and their communities achieve success through a broad range of advice, products and services, including personal and commercial banking, wealth management and private banking, corporate and investment banking, and capital markets.

At Scotiabank, we value the unique skills and experiences each individual brings to the Bank, and are committed to creating and maintaining an inclusive and accessible environment for everyone. If you require accommodation (including, but not limited to, an accessible interview site, alternate format documents, ASL Interpreter, or Assistive Technology) during the recruitment and selection process, please let our Recruitment team know. If you require technical assistance, please click here. Candidates must apply directly online to be considered for this role. We thank all applicants for their interest in a career at Scotiabank; however, only those candidates who are selected for an interview will be contacted.

Title: Junior Data Analyst
Description:
We're on the lookout for an exceptional Junior Data Analyst to join our team at our Toronto Office!




If you're ready to level up and eager to be part of a leading global full-service advertising agency that’s all about high-caliber work, then you're exactly who we're looking for!







The Role:

We are looking for a Junior Level Data Analyst with a strong analytical mindset, excellent communication skills, and the ability to deliver data-driven insights. The ideal candidate will bring proficiency in Excel, a solid understanding of SQL, and strong critical thinking skills. This role also requires the ability to simplify technical concepts for senior leadership. You are passionate about turning data into actionable insights and excel in translating technical findings for diverse audiences.




Sound like you? Read On!




What Your Typical Day Will Look Like:

Employ critical thinking to conduct in-depth data analysis and derive actionable insights and strategic recommendations for optimizing business performance, identify trends, patterns, and opportunities for improvement.
Leverage advanced Excel skills, to organize, analyze, and present data in a clear and comprehensible format.
Apply basic data modelling principles to structure and organize data for analytical purposes.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate data-driven insights into broader business strategies and communicate effectively with internal and external stakeholders, translating complex technical concepts into easily understandable insights.
Monitor data discrepancies, investigate issues, and provide timely solutions to maintain data accuracy.
Help Bridge the gap between technical details and strategic decision-making, particularly when communicating with senior leadership and work collaboratively with cross-functional teams




What You Bring:

Proven experience of 0-1 years in a data analysis role or similar role
Bachelor’s degree in a relevant field (eg. Statistics, Data Science, Business Analytics) or equivalent practical experience
Agency background is an asset
Experience in the Auto industry is a bonus but not a requirement




What You’ll Love About Working At INNOCEAN Canada:

-People-first and Inclusive of all – we’re proud to be recognized by ‘Great Places to Work’ - four years in a row and counting – overall, as well as for youth, inclusion, and as a Best Place to Work for Women.

-Flexible hybrid work set up, with an awesome space at King Street West for collaboration and team get-togethers.

-Generous time off plus an end of year winter break equals time well taken; our people also get extra days off when they reach key work milestones!

-Your Wellbeing is all-important. Our comprehensive plan covers insurance must-haves and nice to haves from full benefits coverage and flex spending account for additional $$$, to RRSP’s confidential individual counseling, and paid personal days for you to take care of you.

-Coaching and mentorship in your day-to-day to fuel your growth.







INNOCEAN Canada is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity, inclusion, and teamwork. We encourage all qualified applicants to inquire below. Any disability-related needs will be accommodated throughout the recruitment process.
